  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mongolia: Combating Gender-Based Violence: Strengthening Justice Sector Capacity</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct beneficiaries: Judges, prosecutors, law enforcement officials, including those from special protection police units, health-care providers, shelter workers and selected civil society organizations (CSOs). Indirect beneficiaries: Victims of GBV.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aimed to support the development of mechanisms to improve a coordinated response to gender-based violence by relevant services providers, and strengthen the capacities of relevant service providers to better respond to gender-based violence.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To strengthen the justice sector capacity to enhance Mongolia&#x2019;s coordinated response to gender-based violence (GBV)</narrative>
  </description>
